title: 1974 United States Senate elections
added: Incumbent Republican [[Peter H. Dominick]] ran for re-election to a third term, but was defeated by Democrat challenger [[Gary Hart]], the campaign manager for [[George McGovern 1972 presidential campaign|George McGovern in 1972]].

title: 1974 United States Senate elections
added: Incumbent Democrat [[Herman Talmadge]] won re-election to a fourth term over Republican challenger Jerry Johnson.

title: 1974 United States Senate elections
added: Incumbent Democratic U.S. Senator [[Adlai Stevenson III]], who was first elected in a special election in 1970, was re-elected to a full term in office, defeating Republican [[George Burdett (lawyer)|George Burditt]] by a large margin of nearly 800,000 votes.
